particularly computational scientists, is speed. In the quest for ways
to make applications run faster, engineers have developed parallel
computers, which use more than one CPU to solve a task. However, many
institutions already posses significant computational power in
networks of workstations. Through software, it is possible to glue
together clusters of machines to simulate a parallel environment.
